"Abstract One of the definitions of the word echelon in the Concise Oxford Dictionary is ‘division of main supply service in warfare’. The Echelon, with a capital ‘E’ that we are concerned about in this article fits nicely into the above definition. The main supply service is electronic surveillance and it is divided between the US, Britain, Australia, New Zealand and Canada. This automated global interception and relay system is responsible for intercepting satellite-based communications."
